      <scopecontent id="aspace_bd3fa9dd2ca5617bb61b34bcb65c5aa0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>A collection of video interviews with leaders of music in the Black church, including pastors, music ministers, gospel artists, and choir directors. These interviews were conducted by students in the Yale University class The Gospel Imagination, taught by Prof. Braxton Shelley.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_8d80a4937f4afacbe87d4ece017e9cb7"
                      localtype="RestrictedSpecColl">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research. The finding aid includes links to stream most interviews online via Oral History of American Music's (OHAM) AV access system, Aviary. Yale users can login to Aviary using their Yale University ID, to stream these interviews without restriction. Other users are able to request access to interviews directly through Aviary. For access instructions, and to request transcripts of an interview, see <ref href="https://guides.library.yale.edu/oham/collectionsguide/access">OHAM's website.</ref>
         </p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_a8d2744569b453cbf142947978b51e5d">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Rights and permissions for Oral History of American Music materials vary between individual interviews. Researchers wishing to publish or broadcast Oral History of American Music materials are responsible for obtaining direct authorization from copyright holders: generally, the interviewees or their estates.</p>
      </userestrict>
      <arrangement id="aspace_a261792ca263fc789d3814985f5816e6">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is arranged alphabetically by surname.</p>
      </arrangement>
      <phystech id="aspace_dced38a281cc7fcbed54acde75a605a6">
